  "description": [
    "By PETER WILLIAMS A twist of medical ethics that works against patients plus fear of encountering racial prejudice may have con tributed to the death of Sam Baroudi 20 who died several hours after he was knocked unconscious by Ezzard Charles in the Stadium last week reported The Chicago Defender The Defenders story pointed out that although Baroudi was dying he was taken to Columbus Memorial Hospitala full 10 miles from the Stadiumand not to a hospital nearer the Stadium because 1 medical ethics dietate that a doctor treat his patient at the hos pital to whose staff he belongs and 2 racial prejudice is so preva lent that there is no assurance Baroudi would have been accepted at another hospital IF YOUVE GOT 120 you can meet dancer Katherine Dunham dance team Jules and Joan Walton and Chicagos blues singer Big Bill Broonzy at Stage for Actions party this Saturday 930 pm International Relations Center 84 E Randolph st t FROM THE AVCs LakeViewpoint bulletin Ye editor is thinking of putting Esq after his name It seems that weve been reprinted Yep the Chicago Star thought that story of Ted Heller and a certain drug storewas pretty good Hiyah"
  ],
